        "subject": "LU-793 ptlrpc: allow client to reconnect with RPC in progress",
        "message": "LU-793 ptlrpc: allow client to reconnect with RPC in progress\n\nSince not letting clients with pending RPCs to reconnect caused a lot\nof problems, this patch allows such a reconnection and would only\nrefuse to process requests with the same xids that are already being\nprocessed.\n\nBulk requests are aborted upon reconnection by comparing connection\ncount of request and export.\n\nLustre-commit: da6a28fc59a70226dd89bac95880f7791f1db075\nLustre-change: http://review.whamcloud.com/4960\n\nThe ptlrpc_request_change_export() is incompatible with recent\nchanges related to LU-793. It moves requests having rq_exp_list\nto the new export exp_hp_req list assuming only hp requests have\nrq_exp_list used, but now all requests use it. That may cause\nnormal requests to be moved to the hp queue.\n\nPatch checks rq_ops instead and move request into proper list.\nSecond change fixes CFS_FAIL_TIMEOUT define, it uses sec * 1000\nbut 'sec' can be expression so it must be (sec) * 1000\n\nLustre-commit: 9db3b77445d8b96f1f4a20ab03a6b8df3aec01e4\nLustre-change: http://review.whamcloud.com/8582\n\nChange-Id: Iba017d9afbe7baf2530631f7781efd6c9de162a2\nSigned-off-by: Mikhail Pershin <mike.pershin@intel.com>\nSigned-off-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@gmail.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_5"
    }
  },
